headline: Cigna Reports Earnings Thursday. The Stock Is Facing Political Uncertainties.
summary: Cigna has outperformed peers as the managed-care industry faces policy challenges. Affordable Care Act subsidies are set to expire and premiums for next year are up 26%.

headline: In Medicare, Less Is Now More for Big Insurers
summary: On Tuesday,  UnitedHealth Group  Chief Executive  Stephen Hemsley  told investors the company is “positioning for durable and accelerating growth in 2026 and beyond.”  One way it is doing that: cutting its Medicare business down to size.  Bobby Hunter,  who oversees  UnitedHealth  care’s government programs, said the insurer expects its Medicare membership to fall by about one million members next year.
